system.description:
ALSO: Final Girl, Target, Whisteblower

These heroes aren’t chosen by destiny or the gods, but rather by the very evil that they will oppose, as Prey. They might have been another forgotten victim, if not for the moment of strength, inspiration, or pure dumb luck that changed their fate.
Now they have a party of allies and a chance, however slim, to strike back at the evil that tried to claim them... as long as they can see past their own fear.

PREY FREE BENEFITS

  • Permanently increase your maximum Hit Points or Mind Points by 5

PREY SKILLS

@UUID[Compendium.fabula-ultima-homebrew.homebrew-skills.Item.Aq4xDd3pP4dQ9fGt]{Cornered Rat (SL3)}

If a creature is blocking you from escaping a scene or restraining you, you deal 【SL × 2】extra damage to them, and get a bonus equal to 【SL】 to Opposed Checks against them.

@UUID[Compendium.fabula-ultima-homebrew.homebrew-skills.Item.IYGc3gbnpqvQBs2y]{Go On Without Me!}

On another creature’s turn in a conflict scene, you may spend 1 Fabula Point to allow that creature to use an Action to escape from the scene, reappearing in a different scene where you or another Player Character is present. Describe how you created the opportunity, and when they reappear, they’ll describe how they got there!

After using this Skill, you can’t use the Rogue Skill See You Later in the same scene, and another character can’t use Go On Without Me! on you. Face your fate.

@UUID[Compendium.fabula-ultima-homebrew.homebrew-skills.Item.aFH53QmpAoUH4aBy]{If It Bleeds… (SL5)}

During a conflict scene, when an ally completes a Clock with a successful Check or an enemy with a rank of elite or above enters Crisis for the first time, choose one: a creature of your choice recovers 【SL × 3】 HP or MP; or the creature who dealt the triggering damage or completed the triggering Clock gains a bonus equal to 【SL】 to their next Check.

@UUID[Compendium.fabula-ultima-homebrew.homebrew-skills.Item.CFyfRtizTPl2mAOd]{Prey Instinct (SL3)}

At the start of a conflict, you may spend 10 Mind Points. If you do, choose one action and perform it before the start of the first round: Guard, Objective, or Study. You gain a bonus equal to 【SL】 to all Checks you perform as part of the chosen action.

You cannot use the Rogue Skill High Speed in the same scene, or vice-versa.

@UUID[Compendium.fabula-ultima-homebrew.homebrew-skills.Item.8EhoBIexhAqyb0ex]{Vigilance or Paranoia (SL4)}

You can identify on sight when soldier-rank creatures are searching for you or mean you harm, but this Skill doesn’t reveal their exact intentions. Describe what tipped you off!

When you are present for the appearance or revelation of a Villain, you may immediately spend a Fabula Point to ask the GM a question about how the party could escape or hinder the Villain (but not to attack or defeat them.) The first Player Character to act on this answer gains a bonus equal to 【SL】 to their Check.

PREY NOTES

@UUID[Compendium.fabula-ultima-homebrew.homebrew-handouts.JournalEntry.fArjgN0xF1QmhtXe]{Prey Rules}

CREDIT

Class Design, Writing and Development Dr. Razno

summary.value: Words are only as good as they actions that follow them.

system.description:
ALSO: Ambassador, Diplomat, Entertainer

Some are graceful and ever smiling, others are subtle and witty: Orators are as good at reading someone’s heart as they are at rounding up allies for their cause, sometimes unintentionally. The words of an Orator may rekindle spirits or plunge their opponents into despair: over the centuries, some Orators’ talents have brought entire nations to ruin… and just as many have granted fallen kingdoms a chance to rise from their very ashes.

ORATOR FREE BENEFITS
  • Permanently increase your maximum Mind Points by 5.

ORATOR SKILLS

@UUID[Compendium.projectfu.skills.Item.DtEiCkDsC1amYABn]{Condemn} (SL4)

You may use an action and spend 5 Mind Points to perform an Opposed 【INS + WLP】 Check against a creature that can hear and understand you — describe your accusations! If you succeed, the target loses 【SL × 10】 Mind Points and suffers dazed or shaken (your choice).

You gain a bonus equal to 【SL】 to your 【INS + WLP】 Checks for this Skill.

@UUID[Compendium.projectfu.skills.Item.04DiGVKhF3DtmJ4n]{Encourage} (SL6)

During a conflict, you may use an action and spend 5 Mind Points to choose another creature that can hear and understand you. That creature recovers 【SL × 5】 Hit Points and chooses Dexterity, Insight, Might, or Willpower: they treat the chosen Attribute as being one die size higher (up to a maximum of d12) until the start of your next turn.

@UUID[Compendium.projectfu.skills.Item.lK9onKSiMuQEe3zd]{My Trust In You} (SL2)

After another Player Character who is able to hear you performs a Check, you may spend 1 Fabula Point and invoke one of their Traits or Bonds in order to let them reroll dice or improve the Result of the Check (following the normal rules). Then, if you have a Bond towards that character, they recover 【SL × 10】 Mind Points.

@UUID[Compendium.projectfu.skills.Item.GjmqoWAJ4szsk0om]{Persuasive} (SL2)

When you successfully perform a Check to fill or erase sections of a Clock, if your approach relied on charm, diplomacy, deception or intimidation, you may spend up to 【SL × 20】 Mind Points. If you do, fill or erase an additional section of that Clock for every 20 Mind Points you spend this way.

@UUID[Compendium.projectfu.skills.Item.ucCrtRAvv2qX8aJO]{Unexpected Ally}

You may use an action and spend 1 Fabula Point to choose a non-hostile creature able to hear and understand you. If you do, that creature becomes helpful towards you so long as you are kind and respectful to them and your requests are reasonable.

summary.value: Borders are a trick of the mind.

system.description:
ALSO: Adventurer, Explorer, Treasure Hunter

Nomads searching for a fabled continent, explorers braving the wilds, grizzled hunters and travelers have one thing in common: they are Wayfarers. While a majority of heroes travel the world during their adventures, Wayfarers live for the journey. They are always eager to visit new places and learn from others. In the eyes of a Wayfarer, the wilderness is neither foe nor an ally, but rather a stern teacher who can reveal many forgotten truths.

WAYFARER FREE BENEFITS
  • Permanently increase your maximum Inventory Points by 2.

WAYFARER SKILLS

@UUID[Compendium.projectfu.skills.Item.L34pOGhdH0ZwV4Bt]{Faithful Companion} (SL5)

Together with the rest of your group, design a level 5 beast, construct, elemental or plant creature (Core Rulebook, page 304) that becomes your companion. This creature has no Initiative score and does not level up, can have up to two basic attacks, gains a bonus equal to 【SL】 to Accuracy Checks and Magic Checks, and their maximum Hit Points are equal to【(SL multiplied by the companion’s base Might die size) + half your level】.

Your companion doesn’t get a turn during conflicts, but on your turn you can use an action to have the companion perform an action (only once per turn). If you leave a scene, your companion leaves with you.

If your companion falls to 0 Hit Points, they flee and rejoin you at the start of the next scene in which you are present, with HP equal to their Crisis score. When you rest, your companion also gains the full benefits of resting.

@UUID[Compendium.projectfu.skills.Item.0n8T7U81oNP7yU5X]{Resourceful} (SL4)

You recover 【SL】 Inventory Points after each travel roll (Core Rulebook, page 106).

@UUID[Compendium.projectfu.skills.Item.CHMsojkTh3fU8HXg]{Tavern Talk} (SL3)

When you rest inside an inn or tavern, you may ask the Game Master up to 【SL】 questions about your surroundings and the people who live here; the Game Master will answer truthfully and you describe how you gathered the information.

@UUID[Compendium.projectfu.skills.Item.rsGhkElIiEBgN5zA]{Treasure Hunter} (SL2)

When your group journeys on the world map, you will make a discovery on a roll of 【SL + 1】 or lower on the travel roll (instead of only on a 1).

@UUID[Compendium.projectfu.skills.Item.fuPzuDHzaKUgbvL2]{Well-Traveled}

You reduce the die rolled for your travel rolls by one size (to a minimum of d6).

If multiple characters have this Skill, the effects are not cumulative.

You may use an action and spend 1 Fabula Point to choose a non-hostile creature able to hear and understand you. If you do, that creature becomes helpful towards you so long as you are kind and respectful to them and your requests are reasonable.

After another Player Character who is able to hear you performs a Check, you may spend 1 Fabula Point and invoke one of their Traits or Bonds in order to let them reroll dice or improve the Result of the Check (following the normal rules). Then, if you have a Bond towards that character, they recover 【SL × 10】 Mind Points.

Skill Level 1 - @GAIN[10 mp]

Skill Level 2 - @GAIN[20 mp]

Together with your group, create a level 5 beast, construct, elemental or plant NPC (see page 302) that becomes your companion: this creature has no initiative score and does not level up, can have a maximum of two basic attacks, gains a bonus equal to 【SL】 to Accuracy Checks and Magic Checks, and their maximum Hit Points are equal to 【(SL, multiplied by the companion's base Might size) + half your level】.

Your companion doesn't get an independent turn during conflicts, but you can use an action to have them perform an action (once per turn). If your companion is affected by any turn-related effects (page 77), these are based on your turn.

Your companion joins and leaves scenes when you do, and gains your same benefits for rests. If reduced to 0 HP, your companion flees the scene and rejoins you at the start of the next scene in which you are present, with current HP equal to their Crisis score.
Automatically equipped in each empty hand slot.
